id_selectors.doc:
The CSS <strong>ID selector</strong> matches an element based on the value of the element's <a href="$MDN_URL$/Web/HTML/Reference/Global_attributes/id"><code>id</code></a> attribute. In order for the element to be selected, its <code>id</code> attribute must match exactly the value given in the selector.
<div>
```css
/* The element with id="demo" */
#demo {
  border: red 2px solid;
}
```
</div>

